If you want to apply a color-burn effect to the actual background used on the page, you can use the CSS filter property. Here’s an example:

body {
  background: radial-gradient(circle at top right, #021, #123, #120, #121, #021);
  filter: brightness(0.6) contrast(1.2);
}

In the above example, the background property sets the radial gradient background with the specified colors. The filter property is then used to modify the brightness and contrast of the background, creating a color-burn effect.

By adjusting the values of the brightness and contrast filters, you can fine-tune the intensity of the color-burn effect. Feel free to experiment with different values to achieve the desired result.

