can you do an intricate anim here to position bg in Y and X?: @keyframes whirlpool {
  0% {background-positionY: 100% 0%;}
  100% {background-positionX: 0% 100%;}
}

Certainly! Here's an example of an intricate animation using the @keyframes rule to animate the background position in the Y and X directions:

@keyframes whirlpool {
  0% {
    background-position: 100% 0%;
  }
  50% {
    background-position: 0% 100%;
  }
  100% {
    background-position: 100% 0%;
  }
}

In the above code, the animation is named "whirlpool" using the @keyframes rule. At the start (0%), the background position is set to 100% on the Y-axis and 0% on the X-axis. At the middle point (50%), the background position is changed to 0% on the Y-axis and 100% on the X-axis. Finally, at the end (100%), the background position is reverted to 100% on the Y-axis and 0% on the X-axis, completing the loop.

You can apply this animation to your desired element using the animation CSS property, specifying the animation duration and any other desired animation properties.

