```
@keyframes whirlpool {
  0% {
    transform: rotate(0deg);
  }
  100% {
    transform: rotate(360deg);
  }
}

.my-element {
  animation: whirlpool 5s linear infinite;
}
```

In the above code, the `@keyframes` rule defines the animation for the `whirlpool` animation. At the start (0%), the background is set with no rotation (0deg), and at the end (100%), it rotates a full 360 degrees using `rotate(360deg)`.

Then, you can apply the animation to your desired element using the `animation` property, specifying the animation name (`whirlpool`), duration (5s), timing function (`linear`), and `infinite` to make it repeat indefinitely.

This will animate the rotation of the background. You can adjust the animation duration and other properties according to your needs.

